Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine buff; rose core; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.200, 28). Name Astymedes. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, KF163/1000163.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1071)
